definition.value: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of pantothenic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A cholestanoid that is 5alpha-cholest-7-ene substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 3 and two methyl groups at position 4.
A ceramide in which the N-acyl moiety bears a hydroxy group alpha- to the carboxamide group.
A sulfonium betaine obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of 3-dimethylsulfoniopropionic acid.
